Trim the root and dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then
thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the @water for the stock{750%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} on high heat. Add
the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}, stir to combine. Bring to the boil then reduce
the heat to the lowest setting. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large
saucepan on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and cook until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}, leek and @sliced mushrooms{120%g}
to the pan. Cook until the veg has softened, ~{4-6%minutes}, then add the garlic
and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The chicken
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are
translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir a ladle of your stock into the rice pan. When the stock has been absorbed by
the rice, stir in another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and
continue stirring in stock, letting it absorb each time.

The cooking time should take ~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your
rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the
middle.

Once cooked, remove the risotto from the heat. Stir in the @peas{120%g}, a knob
of @?butter{knob} and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

When ready, share your chicken and bacon risotto between your #bowls{} with the
remaining cheese sprinkled on top. Enjoy!